{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer truncation in send_is_on function\n\n### Summary\nThe `send_is_on` function in the tracer multiplexer had an implicit integer truncation when assigning the integer literal `1` to a `char` variable. While this didn't cause functional issues since the value 1 fits in a char, static analysis tools were flagging this as a potential narrowing conversion issue.\n\nThe fix makes the type conversion explicit by casting the integer literal to char, eliminating the warning while maintaining identical functionality.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/multi.c`: Changed `char mt = 1;` to `char mt = (char)1;` in the `send_is_on` function to make the narrowing conversion explicit.\n\n"
}